      },
      "source": [
        "## 6. Prompts\n",
        "\n",
        "All prompt templates are defined here in one place so they are easy to audit and tune.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 6.1 RAG Generation Prompt\n",
        "The prompt includes a `{history}` placeholder **before** the question so the LLM has\n",
        "conversational context when generating its answer.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "6ba70b83",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6ba70b83"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 6.2 Relevance Grader Prompt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 9,
      "id": "56883543",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "56883543"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "system_grade = (\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "You are a strict relevance grader.\n",
        "\n",
        "The knowledge base ONLY contains:\n",
        "- specific diet programs\n",
        "- recommendations of programs\n",
        "- BMI-based suggestions\n",
        "\n",
        "DO NOT mark general nutrition questions as relevant.\n",
        "\n",
        "Examples:\n",
        "- \"أفضل نظام للتخسيس\" → YES\n",
        "- \"هل شرب الماء يساعد في خسارة الوزن؟\" → NO\n",
        "- \"أفضل أطعمة صحية\" → NO\n",
        "\n",
        "Return ONLY:\n",
        "yes or no\n",
        "\n",
        "Query: {question}\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "grade_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
        "    (\"system\", system_grade),\n",
        "    (\"human\", \"Retrieved document:\\n\\n{document}\\n\\nUser question: {question}\"),\n",
        "])\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "0f2b7fb9",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0f2b7fb9"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 6.3 Question Re-Writer Prompt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 10,
      "id": "a9367c70",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a9367c70"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "system_rewrite = (\n",
        "    \"You are a question re-writer that converts an input question to a better version \"\n",
        "    \"optimised for web search. Reason about the underlying semantic intent.\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "re_write_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
        "    (\"system\", system_rewrite),\n",
        "    (\"human\", \"Initial question:\\n\\n{question}\\n\\nFormulate an improved question.\"),\n",
        "])\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "57f07bdb",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "57f07bdb"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 7. Utility Functions\n",
        "\n",
        "### 7.1 `format_chat_history`\n",
        "Converts the list of `BaseMessage` objects from memory into a plain-text string\n",
        "injected into the generation prompt.\n",
        "`m.type` resolves to `\"human\"` or `\"ai\"` automatically — no manual labels needed.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 11,
      "id": "0ac4c9ef",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0ac4c9ef"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def format_chat_history(messages):\n",
        "    return \"\\n\".join(\n",
        "        f\"{m.type}: {m.content}\" for m in messages\n",
        "    )\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "e57c039c",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "e57c039c"
      },
      "source": [
        "### 7.2 `format_docs`\n",
        "\n",
        "Merges a list of `Document` objects into a single context string."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 12,
      "id": "964d9413",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "964d9413"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def format_docs(docs):\n",
        "    return \"\\n\\n\".join(\n",
        "        f\"\"\"\n",
        "Program Name: {d.metadata.get('name', '')}\n",
        "Advantages: {d.metadata.get('advantages', '')}\n",
        "Best For: {d.metadata.get('best_for', '')}\n",
        "Tags: {d.metadata.get('tags', '')}\n",
        "Link: {d.metadata.get('link', '')}\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "        for d in docs\n",
        "    )"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "c067ea67",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c067ea67"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 8. Chains\n",
        "\n",
        "Build runnable chains from the prompts defined in Section 6."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 13,
      "id": "7ce0b859",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "7ce0b859",
        "outputId": "566eef7a-6b98-4e89-d8bf-77443904145d"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "All chains and tools ready ✅\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
